      • getPossibleBindingsGivenParamOrderGroups

        public static java.util.List<java.util.List<java.lang.String>> getPossibleBindingsGivenParamOrderGroups(OOState s,
                                                                                                        java.lang.String[] paramClasses,
                                                                                                        java.lang.String[] paramOrderGroups)
        Returns all possible object assignments from a OOState for a given set of parameters that are typed to OO-MDP object classes. For example, parameters for a PropositionalFunction or ObjectParameterizedAction.
        Parameters:
        s - the OOState
        paramClasses - the object class type for a parameter array that needs object assignments
        paramOrderGroups - indicates the order group of a parameter. Parameters in the same order group can have their object assignments shuffled without affecting the evaluation. By default, you probably can have a unique order group for each parameters
        Returns:
        the list of all object assignments, where each object assignment is a list of object names of equal size to the input parameters.
